                        <note>According to the colophon, Wäldä Libanos donated the Ms. to the church Maryam Kädiḥ. The Ms. was completed in the year of the world 7364 (= 1872 A.D.). King Yoḥannǝs IV (r. 1872-89), called ʿAläm Sägäd, and Metropolitan ʾAtnatewos (1869-76) are also mentioned. The scribe was priest (qäsis) Ḫaylä ʾIyäsus from the church of Däbrä Nägäśt ʾAbrǝha wä-ʾAṣbǝḥa.</note>
                     </colophon>
